theorem closure_has_P1_of_P1 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 A → Topology.P1 (closure A) := by
  intro hA
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at hA ⊢
  -- First, `closure A` is contained in `closure (interior A)`
  have h1 : closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) :=
    closure_mono hA
  -- Next, `closure (interior A)` is contained in `closure (interior (closure A))`
  have h2 : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
    have h_int_subset : interior A ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
      interior_mono (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A)
    exact closure_mono h_int_subset
  -- Combining the two inclusions gives the desired result
  exact Set.Subset.trans h1 h2

theorem Topology.P2_iff_P3_of_isOpen
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : IsOpen A) :
    Topology.P2 A ↔ Topology.P3 A := by
  constructor
  · intro hP2
    exact Topology.P2_implies_P3 (X := X) (A := A) hP2
  · intro hP3
    dsimp [Topology.P2, Topology.P3] at hP3 ⊢
    simpa [hA.interior_eq] using hP3
